wfIpBaseCreate.name: wfIpBaseCreate
wfIpBaseCreate.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to create/delete IP.

wfIpBaseEnable.name: wfIpBaseEnable
wfIpBaseEnable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to enable/disable IP.

wfIpBaseState.name: wfIpBaseState
wfIpBaseState.description: The current state of the entire IP.

wfIpBaseForwarding.name: wfIpBaseForwarding
wfIpBaseForwarding.description: The indication of whether this entity is acting as an IP gateway in respect to the forwarding of datagrams received by, but not addressed to, this entity. IP gateways forward datagrams. IP hosts do not (except those source-routed via the host). Note that for some managed nodes, this object may take on only a subset of the values possible. Accordingly, it is appropriate for an agent to return a `badValue' response if a management station attempts to change this object to an inappropriate value.

wfIpBaseDefaultTTL.name: wfIpBaseDefaultTTL
wfIpBaseDefaultTTL.description: The default value inserted into the Time-To-Live field of the IP header of datagrams originated at this entity, whenever a TTL value is not supplied by the transport layer protocol.

wfIpBaseRipDiameter.name: wfIpBaseRipDiameter
wfIpBaseRipDiameter.description: The Diameter of the RIP network. 1 less than 'infinity

wfIpBaseRouteCache.name: wfIpBaseRouteCache
wfIpBaseRouteCache.description: The interval at which routing entries are flushed from the forwarding tables.

wfIpBaseMibTables.name: wfIpBaseMibTables
wfIpBaseMibTables.description: Configures which routing MIB tables are maintained by IP. Previously, only the wfIpBaseRtTable was maintained. In order to support variable length subnets, the wfIpForwardTable was implemented. Supporting both these tables requires memory usage. The user can now configure which tables to maintain to reduce memory usage if needed. In the absence of variable length subnetting, these tables would maintain identical information.

wfIpBaseNetworks.name: wfIpBaseNetworks
wfIpBaseNetworks.description: The number of networks (including subnets) in the routing table

wfIpBaseZeroSubnetEnable.name: wfIpBaseZeroSubnetEnable
wfIpBaseZeroSubnetEnable.description: This parameter indicates whether or not 0 subnets are allowed. If they are not allowed, interfaces configured with a 0 subnet will not be allowed. Value 'rip1onasb' implies 'enabled' also RIP1 support on all one or zero subnet

wfIpBaseEstimatedNetworks.name: wfIpBaseEstimatedNetworks
wfIpBaseEstimatedNetworks.description: This parameter indicates the estimated number of networks that the router will need to keep in its routing table.

wfIpBaseHosts.name: wfIpBaseHosts
wfIpBaseHosts.description: This parameter indicates the number of hosts resolved by IP. This parameter will be equal to the number of instances of wfIpNetToMediaEntry

wfIpBaseEstimatedHosts.name: wfIpBaseEstimatedHosts
wfIpBaseEstimatedHosts.description: This parameter indicates the estimated number of hosts that the router will need to keep in its hosts table.

wfIpBaseDefaultOverSubnetEnable.name: wfIpBaseDefaultOverSubnetEnable
wfIpBaseDefaultOverSubnetEnable.description: This parameter indicates whether or not default route for subnets in subnetted network is allowed.

wfIpBaseMaxPolicyRules.name: wfIpBaseMaxPolicyRules
wfIpBaseMaxPolicyRules.description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of policy rules that can be configured per type (ACCEPT or ANNOUNCE) per protocol. In order to configure more policy rules, this parameter must be changed.

wfIpBaseRouteFilterSupport.name: wfIpBaseRouteFilterSupport
wfIpBaseRouteFilterSupport.description: This parameter indicates whether or not route filters are supported.

wfRipMaximumPath.name: wfRipMaximumPath
wfRipMaximumPath.description: Maximum number of equal cost paths allowed for a network installed by RIP.

wfIpMultipathMethod.name: wfIpMultipathMethod
wfIpMultipathMethod.description: Method to use to choose next hop when more than one is available. The round-robin method will send each packet destined for a given destination to a different nexthop until all have been used, then repeat its iteration through the list. src-dest-hash will use a single nexthop for all traffic originating at one given IP address and addressed to another given IP address. dest-hash is similar but uses only the destination's IP address to compute the nexthop. round-robin provides greater usage of network resources, but increases the chance for out of order packet delivery and similar problems. src-dest-hash increases the chances that packets will be delivered in order, but fails to take full advantage of the capabilities of the network. dest-hash makes the forwarding algorithm compatible with RSVP when the latter is enabled on the router.

wfIpBaseIspMode.name: wfIpBaseIspMode
wfIpBaseIspMode.description: This parameter indicates whether or not ISP features are supported: i.e. BGP soloist, etc.

wfIpBaseExtendedTrafficFilterSupport.name: wfIpBaseExtendedTrafficFilterSupport
wfIpBaseExtendedTrafficFilterSupport.description: This parameter indicates whether or not extended traffic filters are supported.

wfIpOspfMaximumPath.name: wfIpOspfMaximumPath
wfIpOspfMaximumPath.description: Maximum number of equal cost paths allowed for a network installed by OSPF.

wfIpBaseIcmpErrorLimit.name: wfIpBaseIcmpErrorLimit
wfIpBaseIcmpErrorLimit.description: The maximum number of ICMP messages that is allowed to be transmitted within 1 second interval out of any individual interface. Disabled if set to 0.

wfIpBaseIbgpEcmp.name: wfIpBaseIbgpEcmp
wfIpBaseIbgpEcmp.description: IBGP ECMP mode allows BGP to select route to IBGP next hop using available ECMP inter-domain routing information.

wfIpBaseRtbBalanceInterval.name: wfIpBaseRtbBalanceInterval
wfIpBaseRtbBalanceInterval.description: Time interval (in minutes) to re-balance route pool. If this value is 0, then 'periodical re-balance' functionality is considered to be disabled.

wfIpBaseRtblP1.name: wfIpBaseRtblP1
wfIpBaseRtblP1.description: Controls the number of indexes in IP routing RTBL. If this value is 0, a value based on the number of hosts and the number of nets will be calculated. This parameter is closely linked with wfIpBaseRtblP2 in terms of balancing the rtbl

wfIpBaseRtblP2.name: wfIpBaseRtblP2
wfIpBaseRtblP2.description: Controls the deviation of nodes per index from the average number of nodes per index. If this value is 0, a value based on the number of hosts and the number of nets will be calculated. This parameter is closely linked with wfIpBaseRtblP1 in terms of balancing the rtbl

wfIpBaseArpBufLimitPrcnt.name: wfIpBaseArpBufLimitPrcnt
wfIpBaseArpBufLimitPrcnt.description: Defines the upper limit (in percent) of buffers that can be used by ARP for saving buffers when resolving ARP request

wfIpBaseDirectedBcastEnable.name: wfIpBaseDirectedBcastEnable
wfIpBaseDirectedBcastEnable.description: Boxwide directed broadcast Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled.

wfIpBaseHostOnlyRip.name: wfIpBaseHostOnlyRip
wfIpBaseHostOnlyRip.description: Whether or not listen RIPs in Host Only Mode.

wfIpBaseBlockSRR.name: wfIpBaseBlockSRR
wfIpBaseBlockSRR.description: Blocks incoming IP packets that have the Loose or Strict Source Record Route ip option enabled. Default is disabled which will allow these packets through.

wfIpBaseRtEntryTable.name: wfIpBaseRtEntryTable
wfIpBaseRtEntryTable.description: The list of elements in IP's routing table

wfIpBaseRouteDest.name: wfIpBaseRouteDest
wfIpBaseRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. An entry with a value of 0.0.0.0 is considered a default route. Multiple routes to a single destination can appear in the table, but access to such multiple entries is dependent on the table- access mechanisms defined by the network management protocol in use.

wfIpBaseRouteIfIndex.name: wfIpBaseRouteIfIndex
wfIpBaseRouteIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wfIpBaseRouteMetric1.name: wfIpBaseRouteMetric1
wfIpBaseRouteMetric1.description: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpBaseRouteMetric2.name: wfIpBaseRouteMetric2
wfIpBaseRouteMetric2.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpBaseRouteMetric3.name: wfIpBaseRouteMetric3
wfIpBaseRouteMetric3.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpBaseRouteMetric4.name: wfIpBaseRouteMetric4
wfIpBaseRouteMetric4.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpBaseRouteNextHop.name: wfIpBaseRouteNextHop
wfIpBaseRouteNextHop.description: The IP address of the next hop of this route. (In the case of a route bound to an interface which is realized via a broadcast media, the value of this field is the agent's IP address on that interface.)

wfIpBaseRouteType.name: wfIpBaseRouteType
wfIpBaseRouteType.description: The type of route. Note that the values direct(3) and indirect(4) refer to the notion of direct and indirect routing in the IP architecture. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the ipRouteTable object. That is, it effectively dissasociates the destination identified with said entry from the route identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. nagement stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant ipRouteType object.

wfIpBaseRouteProto.name: wfIpBaseRouteProto
wfIpBaseRouteProto.description: The routing mechanism via which this route was learned. Inclusion of values for gateway routing protocols is not intended to imply that hosts should support those protocols.

wfIpBaseRouteAge.name: wfIpBaseRouteAge
wfIpBaseRouteAge.description: The number of seconds since this route was last updated or otherwise determined to be correct. Note that no semantics of `too old' can be implied except through knowledge of the routing protocol by which the route was learned.

wfIpBaseRouteMask.name: wfIpBaseRouteMask
wfIpBaseRouteMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the ipRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the ipRouteMask by determining whether the value of the correspondent ipRouteDest field belong to a class-A, B, or C network, and then using one of: mask network 255.0.0.0 class-A 255.255.0.0 class-B 255.255.255.0 class-C If the value of the ipRouteDest is 0.0.0.0 (a default route), then the mask value is also 0.0.0.0. It should be noted that all IP routing subsystems implicitly use this mechanism.

wfIpBaseRouteMetric5.name: wfIpBaseRouteMetric5
wfIpBaseRouteMetric5.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpBaseRouteInfo.name: wfIpBaseRouteInfo
wfIpBaseRouteInfo.description: A user-defined string which describes this Route entry

wfIpBaseHostEntryTable.name: wfIpBaseHostEntryTable
wfIpBaseHostEntryTable.description: The list of elements in IP's host table

wfIpBaseHostEntry.name: wfIpBaseHostEntry
wfIpBaseHostEntry.description: A description of a resolved host

wfIpBaseNetToMediaIfIndex.name: wfIpBaseNetToMediaIfIndex
wfIpBaseNetToMediaIfIndex.description: The interface on which this entry's equivalence is effective. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wfIpBaseNetToMediaNetAddress.name: wfIpBaseNetToMediaNetAddress
wfIpBaseNetToMediaNetAddress.description: The IpAddress corresponding to the media-dependent `physical' address.

wfIpBaseNetToMediaType.name: wfIpBaseNetToMediaType
wfIpBaseNetToMediaType.description: The type of mapping. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the ipNetToMediaTable. That is, it effectively dissasociates the interface identified with said entry from the mapping identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant ipNetToMediaType object.

wfIpInterfaceTable.name: wfIpInterfaceTable
wfIpInterfaceTable.description: The list of configured IP interface

wfIpInterfaceCreate.name: wfIpInterfaceCreate
wfIpInterfaceCreate.description: Create/Delete parameter. Default is created. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to create/delete an IP interface.

wfIpInterfaceEnable.name: wfIpInterfaceEnable
wfIpInterfaceEnable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is enabled. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to enable/disable an IP interface.

wfIpInterfaceState.name: wfIpInterfaceState
wfIpInterfaceState.description: INvalid indicates an error in processing the cfg record

wfIpInterfaceAddr.name: wfIpInterfaceAddr
wfIpInterfaceAddr.description: The IP Address to which this entry's addressing information pertains

wfIpInterfaceCircuit.name: wfIpInterfaceCircuit
wfIpInterfaceCircuit.description: The Circuit Number that this interface runs over

wfIpInterfaceMask.name: wfIpInterfaceMask
wfIpInterfaceMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

wfIpInterfaceCost.name: wfIpInterfaceCost
wfIpInterfaceCost.description: The Cost metric associated with the IP Address of this entry

wfIpInterfaceCfgBcastAddr.name: wfIpInterfaceCfgBcastAddr
wfIpInterfaceCfgBcastAddr.description: The user can specifcy a broadcast address for a NWIF

wfIpInterfaceBcastAddr.name: wfIpInterfaceBcastAddr
wfIpInterfaceBcastAddr.description: The value of the broadcast address used for sending datagrams on the (logical) interface associated with the IP address of this entry. This value applies to both the subnet and network broadcasts addresses used by the entity on this (logical) interface. This is value used by the software

wfIpInterfaceMTUDiscovery.name: wfIpInterfaceMTUDiscovery
wfIpInterfaceMTUDiscovery.description: Whether MTU discovery option is on/off

wfIpInterfaceAMR.name: wfIpInterfaceAMR
wfIpInterfaceAMR.description: Whether Address Mask Reply is ON/OFF

wfIpInterfaceASB.name: wfIpInterfaceASB
wfIpInterfaceASB.description: Whether All-Subnet Broadcasts Are excepted and Sent out this NWIF

wfIpInterfaceAddressResolutionType.name: wfIpInterfaceAddressResolutionType
wfIpInterfaceAddressResolutionType.description: Indicates which Address Resolution Type to use

wfIpInterfaceProxy.name: wfIpInterfaceProxy
wfIpInterfaceProxy.description: Indicates Whether Proxy is on this Interface or not

wfIpInterfaceHostCache.name: wfIpInterfaceHostCache
wfIpInterfaceHostCache.description: Whether the Host Cache (Address Aging) is on or not. A Range of discrete values is specified as well as a value meaning don't age

wfIpInterfaceUdpXsumOn.name: wfIpInterfaceUdpXsumOn
wfIpInterfaceUdpXsumOn.description: Whether to turn UDP checksum verification on for UDP packets recieved and transmitted by this router

wfIpInterfaceCfgMacAddress.name: wfIpInterfaceCfgMacAddress
wfIpInterfaceCfgMacAddress.description: The desired mac set by the user

wfIpInterfaceMacAddress.name: wfIpInterfaceMacAddress
wfIpInterfaceMacAddress.description: The MAC Address for this Interface- actual one used

wfIpInterfaceReasmMaxSize.name: wfIpInterfaceReasmMaxSize
wfIpInterfaceReasmMaxSize.description: The size of the largest IP datagram which this entity can re-assemble from incoming IP fragmented datagrams received on this interface.

wfIpInterfaceMaxInfo.name: wfIpInterfaceMaxInfo
wfIpInterfaceMaxInfo.description: The maximum size of the INFO (non-MAC) field that this port will receive or transmit.

wfIpInterfaceInReceives.name: wfIpInterfaceInReceives
wfIpInterfaceInReceives.description: The total number of input datagrams received from interfaces, including those received in error.

wfIpInterfaceInHdrErrors.name: wfIpInterfaceInHdrErrors
wfIpInterfaceInHdrErrors.description: The number of input datagrams discarded due to errors in their IP headers, including bad checksums, version number mismatch, other format errors, time-to-live exceeded, errors discovered in processing their IP options, etc.

wfIpInterfaceInAddrErrors.name: wfIpInterfaceInAddrErrors
wfIpInterfaceInAddrErrors.description: The number of input datagrams discarded because the IP address in their IP header's destination field was not a valid address to be received at this entity. This count includes invalid addresses (e.g., 0.0.0.0) and addresses of unsupported Classes (e.g., Class E). For entities which are not IP Gateways and therefore do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams discarded because the destination address was not a local address.

wfIpInterfaceForwDatagrams.name: wfIpInterfaceForwDatagrams
wfIpInterfaceForwDatagrams.description: The number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination, as a result of which an attempt was made to find a route to forward them to that final destination. In entities which do not act as IP Gateways, this counter will include only those packets which were Source-Routed via this entity, and the Source- Route option processing was successful.

wfIpInterfaceInUnknownProtos.name: wfIpInterfaceInUnknownProtos
wfIpInterfaceInUnknownProtos.description: The number of locally-addressed datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

wfIpInterfaceInDiscards.name: wfIpInterfaceInDiscards
wfIpInterfaceInDiscards.description: The number of input IP datagrams for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but which were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter does not include any datagrams discarded while awaiting re-assembly.

wfIpInterfaceInDelivers.name: wfIpInterfaceInDelivers
wfIpInterfaceInDelivers.description: The total number of input datagrams successfully delivered to IP user-protocols (including ICMP).

wfIpInterfaceOutRequests.name: wfIpInterfaceOutRequests
wfIpInterfaceOutRequests.description: The total number of IP datagrams which local IP user-protocols (including ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. Note that this counter does not include any datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams.

wfIpInterfaceOutDiscards.name: wfIpInterfaceOutDiscards
wfIpInterfaceOutDiscards.description: The number of output IP datagrams for which no problem was encountered to prevent their transmission to their destination, but which were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter would include datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams if any such packets met this (discretionary) discard criterion.

wfIpInterfaceOutNoRoutes.name: wfIpInterfaceOutNoRoutes
wfIpInterfaceOutNoRoutes.description: The number of IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Note that this counter includes any packets counted in ipForwDatagrams which meet this `no-route' criterion. Note that this includes any datagarms which a host cannot route because all of its default gateways are down.

wfIpInterfaceReasmTimeout.name: wfIpInterfaceReasmTimeout
wfIpInterfaceReasmTimeout.description: The maximum number of seconds which received fragments are held while they are awaiting reassembly at this entity.

wfIpInterfaceReasmReqds.name: wfIpInterfaceReasmReqds
wfIpInterfaceReasmReqds.description: The number of IP fragments received which needed to be reassembled at this entity.

wfIpInterfaceReasmOKs.name: wfIpInterfaceReasmOKs
wfIpInterfaceReasmOKs.description: The number of IP datagrams successfully reassembled.

wfIpInterfaceReasmFails.name: wfIpInterfaceReasmFails
wfIpInterfaceReasmFails.description: The number of failures detected by the IP re- assembly algorithm (for whatever reason: timed out, errors, etc). Note that this is not necessarily a count of discarded IP fragments since some algorithms (notably the algorithm in RFC 815) can lose track of the number of fragments by combining them as they are received.

wfIpInterfaceFragOKs.name: wfIpInterfaceFragOKs
wfIpInterfaceFragOKs.description: The number of IP datagrams that have been successfully fragmented at this entity.

wfIpInterfaceFragFails.name: wfIpInterfaceFragFails
wfIpInterfaceFragFails.description: The number of IP datagrams that have been discarded because they needed to be fragmented at this entity but could not be, e.g., because their Don't Fragment flag was set.

wfIpInterfaceFragCreates.name: wfIpInterfaceFragCreates
wfIpInterfaceFragCreates.description: The number of IP datagram fragments that have been generated as a result of fragmentation at this entity.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInMsgs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInMsgs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInMsgs.description: The total number of ICMP messages which includes all those counted by wfIpInterfaceIcmpInErrors.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInErrors.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInErrors
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInErrors.description: The number of ICMP messages which the entity received but determined as having ICMP-specific errors (bad ICMP checksums, bad length, etc.).

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInDestUnreachs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInDestUnreachs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInDestUnreachs.description: The number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimeExcds.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimeExcds
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimeExcds.description: The number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInParmProbs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInParmProbs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInParmProbs.description: The number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInSrcQuenchs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInSrcQuenchs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInSrcQuenchs.description: The number of ICMP Source Quench messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInRedirects.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInRedirects
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInRedirects.description: The number of ICMP Redirect messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInEchos.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInEchos
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInEchos.description: The number of ICMP Echo (request) messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInEchoReps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInEchoReps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInEchoReps.description: The number of ICMP Echo Reply messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimestamps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimestamps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimestamps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp (request) messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimestampReps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimestampReps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInTimestampReps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp Reply messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInAddrMasks.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInAddrMasks
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInAddrMasks.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Request messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInAddrMaskReps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInAddrMaskReps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInAddrMaskReps.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Reply messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutMsgs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutMsgs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutMsgs.description: The total number of ICMP messages which this entity attempted to send. Note that this counter includes all those counted by icmpOutErrors.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutErrors.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutErrors
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutErrors.description: The number of ICMP messages which this entity did not send due to problems discovered within ICMP such as a lack of buffers. This value should not include errors discovered outside the ICMP layer such as the inability of IP to route the resultant datagram. In some implementations there may be no types of error which contribute to this counter's value.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutDestUnreachs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutDestUnreachs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutDestUnreachs.description: The number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimeExcds.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimeExcds
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimeExcds.description: The number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutParmProbs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutParmProbs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutParmProbs.description: The number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutSrcQuenchs.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutSrcQuenchs
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutSrcQuenchs.description: The number of ICMP Source Quench messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutRedirects.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutRedirects
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutRedirects.description: The number of ICMP Redirect messages sent. For a host, this object will always be zero, since hosts do not send redirects.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutEchos.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutEchos
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutEchos.description: The number of ICMP Echo (request) messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutEchoReps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutEchoReps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutEchoReps.description: The number of ICMP Echo Reply messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimestamps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimestamps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimestamps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp (request) messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimestampReps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimestampReps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutTimestampReps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp Reply messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutAddrMasks.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutAddrMasks
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutAddrMasks.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Request messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutAddrMaskReps.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutAddrMaskReps
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutAddrMaskReps.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Reply messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceTrEndStation.name: wfIpInterfaceTrEndStation
wfIpInterfaceTrEndStation.description: Use Source Routing over token ring selection. Only applies if pam type is TRING.

wfIpInterfaceRedirect.name: wfIpInterfaceRedirect
wfIpInterfaceRedirect.description: Indicates Whether we're sending out redirects on this Interface or not

wfIpInterfaceEnetArpEncaps.name: wfIpInterfaceEnetArpEncaps
wfIpInterfaceEnetArpEncaps.description: The data link encapsulation type to use for ARP packets if the the media is ethernet.

wfIpInterfaceCacheMisses.name: wfIpInterfaceCacheMisses
wfIpInterfaceCacheMisses.description: The number of FFT cache misses (i.e how many times did the cache gate have to do a look up in the RNP because the FFT didn't have the destination network

wfIpInterfaceCacheRemoves.name: wfIpInterfaceCacheRemoves
wfIpInterfaceCacheRemoves.description: The number of networks which have been flushed from the FFT because of aging

wfIpInterfaceSlotMask.name: wfIpInterfaceSlotMask
wfIpInterfaceSlotMask.description: Slot mask for which slots a circuit-less interface is eligible to run on. The most significant bit represents slot 1, the next most significant bit represents slot 2, and so on... Slots can be 1-14. This is only valid if wfIpInterfaceCircuit is 0.

wfIpInterfaceStripSecurity.name: wfIpInterfaceStripSecurity
wfIpInterfaceStripSecurity.description: Defines which packets will have security option removed. This is a bit mask.

wfIpInterfaceRequireOutSecurity.name: wfIpInterfaceRequireOutSecurity
wfIpInterfaceRequireOutSecurity.description: Defines which types of outbound packets are required to have a security option. This is a bit mask.

wfIpInterfaceRequireInSecurity.name: wfIpInterfaceRequireInSecurity
wfIpInterfaceRequireInSecurity.description: Defines whether or not incoming packets must have security option. This is a bit mask.

wfIpInterfaceMinLevel.name: wfIpInterfaceMinLevel
wfIpInterfaceMinLevel.description: Defines the minimum level allowed for packets transmitted or received via this interface. IP_NWIF_LEVEL_UNCLASSIFIED 171 0x000000AB IP_NWIF_LEVEL_CONFIDENTIAL 150 0x00000096 IP_NWIF_LEVEL_SECRET 90 0x0000005A IP_NWIF_LEVEL_TOPSECRET 61 0x0000003D

wfIpInterfaceMaxLevel.name: wfIpInterfaceMaxLevel
wfIpInterfaceMaxLevel.description: Defines the maximum level allowed for packets transmitted or received via this interface. IP_NWIF_LEVEL_UNCLASSIFIED 171 0x000000AB IP_NWIF_LEVEL_CONFIDENTIAL 150 0x00000096 IP_NWIF_LEVEL_SECRET 90 0x0000005A IP_NWIF_LEVEL_TOPSECRET 61 0x0000003D

wfIpInterfaceMustOutAuthority.name: wfIpInterfaceMustOutAuthority
wfIpInterfaceMustOutAuthority.description: Defines the authority bits that must be set in packets transmitted via this interface. This is a bit map. Zero is valid. Authorities have been defined for the first octet. This is represented by the following 'bit mask' values. IP_NWIF_AUTH_NONE 0 (0x00) IP_NWIF_AUTH_GENSER 128 (0x80) IP_NWIF_AUTH_SIOPESI 64 (0x40) IP_NWIF_AUTH_SCI 32 (0x20) IP_NWIF_AUTH_NSA 16 (0x10) IP_NWIF_AUTH_DOE 8 (0x08) IP_NWIF_AUTH_ALL 248 (0xF8) If no value is specified, the software will default to IP_NWIF_AUTH_NONE.

wfIpInterfaceMayOutAuthority.name: wfIpInterfaceMayOutAuthority
wfIpInterfaceMayOutAuthority.description: Defines the authority bits that may be set in packets transmitted via this interface. This is a bit map. Zero is valid. Authorities have been defined for the first octet. This is represented by the following 'bit mask' values. wfIpInterfaceMustInAuthority.name: wfIpInterfaceMustInAuthority

wfIpInterfaceMayInAuthority.name: wfIpInterfaceMayInAuthority

wfIpInterfaceImplicitLabelEnabled.name: wfIpInterfaceImplicitLabelEnabled
wfIpInterfaceImplicitLabelEnabled.description: Should an implicit label be associated with any inbound unlabelled datagrams?

wfIpInterfaceImplicitAuth.name: wfIpInterfaceImplicitAuth
wfIpInterfaceImplicitAuth.description: Defines the authority bits in the implicit label associated with an unlabelled inbound datagram. This is a bit map. 'NONE' means that a 3-byte option label (no authority byte) is used. This field only has meaning if implicit labelling is enabled (wfIpInterfaceImplicitLabelEnabled = IP_NWIF_LABEL_ENABLED). The octets indicate auth values. Authorities have been defined for the first octet. This is represented by the following 'bit mask' values: IP_NWIF_AUTH_NONE 0 (0x00) IP_NWIF_AUTH_GENSER 128 (0x80) IP_NWIF_AUTH_SIOPESI 64 (0x40) IP_NWIF_AUTH_SCI 32 (0x20) IP_NWIF_AUTH_NSA 16 (0x10) IP_NWIF_AUTH_DOE 8 (0x08) IP_NWIF_AUTH_ALL 248 (0xF8) If no value is specified and implicit labelling is enabled, the software defaults to IP_NWIF_AUTH_NONE.

wfIpInterfaceImplicitLevel.name: wfIpInterfaceImplicitLevel
wfIpInterfaceImplicitLevel.description: Defines the classification level byte in the implicit label associated with an unlabelled inbound datagram. IP_NWIF_LEVEL_UNCLASSIFIED 171 0x000000AB IP_NWIF_LEVEL_CONFIDENTIAL 150 0x00000096 IP_NWIF_LEVEL_SECRET 90 0x0000005A IP_NWIF_LEVEL_TOPSECRET 61 0x0000003D

wfIpInterfaceDefaultLabelEnabled.name: wfIpInterfaceDefaultLabelEnabled
wfIpInterfaceDefaultLabelEnabled.description: Should a default label be associated with any not-yet-labelled oubound datagrams?

wfIpInterfaceDefaultAuth.name: wfIpInterfaceDefaultAuth
wfIpInterfaceDefaultAuth.description: Defines the authority bits in the default label associated with a not-yet-labelled outbound datagram. This is a bit map. 'NONE' means that a 3-byte option label (no authority byte) is used. This field only has meaning if default labelling is enabled (wfIpInterfaceDefaultLabelEnabled = IP_NWIF_LABEL_ENABLED). The octets indicate auth values. Authorities have been defined for the first octet. This is represented by the following 'bit mask' values: IP_NWIF_AUTH_NONE 0 (0x00) IP_NWIF_AUTH_GENSER 128 (0x80) IP_NWIF_AUTH_SIOPESI 64 (0x40) IP_NWIF_AUTH_SCI 32 (0x20) IP_NWIF_AUTH_NSA 16 (0x10) IP_NWIF_AUTH_DOE 8 (0x08) IP_NWIF_AUTH_ALL 248 (0xF8) If no value is specified and default labelling is enabled, the software defaults to IP_NWIF_AUTH_NONE.

wfIpInterfaceDefaultLevel.name: wfIpInterfaceDefaultLevel
wfIpInterfaceDefaultLevel.description: Defines the classification level byte to use in the default label associated with a not-yet-labelled outbound datagram. IP_NWIF_LEVEL_UNCLASSIFIED 171 0x000000AB IP_NWIF_LEVEL_CONFIDENTIAL 150 0x00000096 IP_NWIF_LEVEL_SECRET 90 0x0000005A IP_NWIF_LEVEL_TOPSECRET 61 0x0000003D

wfIpInterfaceErrorLabelEnabled.name: wfIpInterfaceErrorLabelEnabled
wfIpInterfaceErrorLabelEnabled.description: Should an error label be associated with any outbound ICMP error packets?

wfIpInterfaceErrorAuth.name: wfIpInterfaceErrorAuth
wfIpInterfaceErrorAuth.description: Defines the authority bits in the error label associated with any outbount ICMP error packets. This is a bit map. 'NONE' means that a 3-byte option label (no authority byte) is used. This field only has meaning if error labelling is enabled (wfIpInterfaceErrorLabelEnabled = IP_NWIF_LABEL_ENABLED). The octets indicate auth values. Authorities have been defined for the first octet. This is represented by the following 'bit mask' values: IP_NWIF_AUTH_NONE 0 (0x00) IP_NWIF_AUTH_GENSER 128 (0x80) IP_NWIF_AUTH_SIOPESI 64 (0x40) IP_NWIF_AUTH_SCI 32 (0x20) IP_NWIF_AUTH_NSA 16 (0x10) IP_NWIF_AUTH_DOE 8 (0x08) IP_NWIF_AUTH_ALL 248 (0xF8) If no value is specified and error labelling is enabled, the software defaults to IP_NWIF_AUTH_NONE

wfIpInterfaceDropRxAuths.name: wfIpInterfaceDropRxAuths
wfIpInterfaceDropRxAuths.description: Number of received packets dropped because the authority flag(s) were not sufficient. This could mean that the 'must' flags were not all there, or that the flags other than the 'may' flags were specified.

wfIpInterfaceDropRxFormats.name: wfIpInterfaceDropRxFormats
wfIpInterfaceDropRxFormats.description: Number of received packets dropped because the security option format was invalid.

wfIpInterfaceDropRxLevels.name: wfIpInterfaceDropRxLevels
wfIpInterfaceDropRxLevels.description: Number of received packets dropped because the classification level was out of range.

wfIpInterfaceDropRxNoIpsos.name: wfIpInterfaceDropRxNoIpsos
wfIpInterfaceDropRxNoIpsos.description: Number of received packets dropped because no IP security label was present.

wfIpInterfaceDropTxAuths.name: wfIpInterfaceDropTxAuths
wfIpInterfaceDropTxAuths.description: Number of transmitted packets dropped because the authority flag(s) were not sufficient. This could mean that the 'must' flags were not all there, or that the flags other than the 'may' flags were specified.

wfIpInterfaceDropTxLevels.name: wfIpInterfaceDropTxLevels
wfIpInterfaceDropTxLevels.description: Number of transmitted packets dropped because the classification level was out of range.

wfIpInterfaceDropTxNoIpsos.name: wfIpInterfaceDropTxNoIpsos
wfIpInterfaceDropTxNoIpsos.description: Number of packets not transmitted because no IP security label was present.

wfIpInterfaceDropTxNoIpsoRooms.name: wfIpInterfaceDropTxNoIpsoRooms
wfIpInterfaceDropTxNoIpsoRooms.description: Number of packets not transmitted because there was not enough space left in the IP header to insert an IP security option.

wfIpInterfaceICMPInAdminProhib.name: wfIpInterfaceICMPInAdminProhib
wfIpInterfaceICMPInAdminProhib.description: Number of ICMP dest unreachable/communication administratively prohibited messages received. Note: may be sent by BFE or another system

wfIpInterfaceICMPOutAdminProhib.name: wfIpInterfaceICMPOutAdminProhib
wfIpInterfaceICMPOutAdminProhib.description: Number of ICMP dest unreachable/communication administratively prohibited messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceFwdCacheSize.name: wfIpInterfaceFwdCacheSize
wfIpInterfaceFwdCacheSize.description: Maximum number of entries allowed in the Forwarding Table at one time. There is a forwarding table per interface.

wfIpInterfaceTunnelInfo.name: wfIpInterfaceTunnelInfo
wfIpInterfaceTunnelInfo.description: If non-null and if wfIpInterfaceCircuit is zero, this string contains encoded information for setting up this interface as a tunnel endpoint. Currently, no underlying code has been implemented for this feature.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInRdiscSolicit.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInRdiscSolicit
wfIpInterfaceIcmpInRdiscSolicit.description: The number of ICMP Router Discovery Solicit messages received.

wfIpInterfaceIcmpInRdiscAdvert.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpInRdiscAdvert

wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutRdiscAdvert.name: wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutRdiscAdvert
wfIpInterfaceIcmpOutRdiscAdvert.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Reply messages sent.

wfIpInterfaceRoutingDiscards.name: wfIpInterfaceRoutingDiscards
wfIpInterfaceRoutingDiscards.description: The number of routing entries which were chosen to be discarded even though they are valid

wfIpInterfaceUnnumAssocAddr.name: wfIpInterfaceUnnumAssocAddr
wfIpInterfaceUnnumAssocAddr.description: The Associated IP address used by unnumbered interfaces when sourcing a packet. Rip also uses this attribute to make decisions about advertising subnets over unnumbered interfaces. Rip will advertise subnets over the unnumbered interface if they have the same mask as the associated address.

wfIpInterfaceUnnumAssocAlt.name: wfIpInterfaceUnnumAssocAlt
wfIpInterfaceUnnumAssocAlt.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Default is disabled. Users perform a set operation on this object in order to enable/disable the option to automatically assign an alternate unnumbered associated address in the event that the primary associated address interface has gone down

wfIpInterfaceAtmArpMode.name: wfIpInterfaceAtmArpMode
wfIpInterfaceAtmArpMode.description: Indicates whether ATMARP is a client or running as a server. A value of 'none' is for ATM WAN SVCs feature

wfIpInterfaceAtmArpServerVcAgingEnable.name: wfIpInterfaceAtmArpServerVcAgingEnable
wfIpInterfaceAtmArpServerVcAgingEnable.description: Indicates whether the ATMARP server VC should be aged (for client operation)

wfIpInterfaceAtmArpServerRegInterval.name: wfIpInterfaceAtmArpServerRegInterval
wfIpInterfaceAtmArpServerRegInterval.description: For client operation, the interval between registration refreshes. For a server. this will be the duration a registration is valid. (in seconds)

wfIpInterfaceAtmArpServerConnState.name: wfIpInterfaceAtmArpServerConnState
wfIpInterfaceAtmArpServerConnState.description: Indicates the state of the connection to the ATMARP server. This field should be interpreted as follows (bit 31 is msb, bit 0 is lsb): bits 0-3 are bits for determining ATMARP initialization, client/server, and if the client has ARP requests to send to the server: 0x001 INIT 0x002 WERESERVER 0x--4 CLIENT 0x--8 HAVEARPTOSEND bits 4-7 represent the state of the VC to the server: 0x-0- CLOSED 0x-1- OPENING 0x-2- OPEN 0x-3- OPENFAILED bits 8-11 represent the state of registration to the server: 0x0-- NOTREGISTERED 0x1-- REGISTERING 0x2-- REGISTERED 0x3-- REGISTRATIONFAILED 0x4-- NOSERVER

wfIpInterfaceAtmArpAttemptedCalls.name: wfIpInterfaceAtmArpAttemptedCalls

wfIpInterfaceAtmArpFailRetryCalls.name: wfIpInterfaceAtmArpFailRetryCalls
wfIpInterfaceAtmArpFailRetryCalls.description: Indicates the number of attempted calls that have failed, but were retried

wfIpInterfaceAtmArpFailNoRetryCalls.name: wfIpInterfaceAtmArpFailNoRetryCalls
wfIpInterfaceAtmArpFailNoRetryCalls.description: Indicates the number of attempted calls that have failed, and were not retried

wfIpInterfaceAtmArpSuccessfulCalls.name: wfIpInterfaceAtmArpSuccessfulCalls
wfIpInterfaceAtmArpSuccessfulCalls.description: Indicates the number of originated calls completed successfully

wfIpInterfaceAtmArpAcceptedCalls.name: wfIpInterfaceAtmArpAcceptedCalls
wfIpInterfaceAtmArpAcceptedCalls.description: Indicates the number of received calls that were accepted

wfIpInterfaceAtmArpOpenSvcs.name: wfIpInterfaceAtmArpOpenSvcs
wfIpInterfaceAtmArpOpenSvcs.description: Indicates the number of currently open calls

wfIpInterfaceTrEsArpType.description: Token Ring End Station ARP type ARE / STE

wfIpSrCost.name: wfIpSrCost

wfIpSrIpAddressRt.name: wfIpSrIpAddressRt
wfIpSrIpAddressRt.description: The Route Identifier Which numbered route this is to be

wfIpSrValid.name: wfIpSrValid

wfIpSrUnnumCct.name: wfIpSrUnnumCct

wfIpAdjacentHostTable.description: The list of Adjacent Hosts (static IP-Mac resolutions)

wfIpAdjacentHostEntry.description: A description of an adjacent host

wfIpAdjHostMacAddr.description: The LAN Address for this HOST

wfIpAdjHostEncaps.description: The encapsulation type of this entry

wfIpAdjHostValid.description: Whether the record passed validation or not

wfIpAdjHostX121Addr.description: WAN address (X.121, E.164, etc.) used to establish an SVC to the adjacent host.

wfIpAdjHostSubaddr.name: wfIpAdjHostSubaddr
wfIpAdjHostSubaddr.description: The subaddress used to establish an SVC to the adjacent host.

wfIpAdjHostTypeOfNumber.name: wfIpAdjHostTypeOfNumber
wfIpAdjHostTypeOfNumber.description: The type of number used to establish an SVC to the adjacent host.

wfIpAdjHostGreConnName.name: wfIpAdjHostGreConnName
wfIpAdjHostGreConnName.description: The name of the remote GRE connection to which an adjacent host is configured.

wfIpTrafficFilterCreate.description: Defines the existence of the traffic filter rule: created - traffic filter exists delete - traffic filter does not exist and can be deleted.

wfIpTrafficFilterEnable.description: Defines whether or not the traffic filter rule should be used: enabled - activate the rule. disabled - inactivate the rule.

wfIpTrafficFilterStatus.name: wfIpTrafficFilterStatus
wfIpTrafficFilterStatus.description: Defines the current status of the traffic filter: inactive - the rule is not in use. active - the rule is being used. error - the application detected an error in the rule.

wfIpTrafficFilterCounter.name: wfIpTrafficFilterCounter
wfIpTrafficFilterCounter.description: The number of received packets that have matched this rule.

wfIpTrafficFilterInterface.name: wfIpTrafficFilterInterface
wfIpTrafficFilterInterface.description: The network address of the IP interface to which this filter is applied.

wfIpTrafficFilterCircuit.name: wfIpTrafficFilterCircuit
wfIpTrafficFilterCircuit.description: The ID of the Circuit to which the filter is applied.

wfIpTrafficFilterPrecedence.name: wfIpTrafficFilterPrecedence
wfIpTrafficFilterPrecedence.description: Precedence of the filter. If 2 or more rules match the one with higher precedence will be applied.

wfIpTrafficFilterDSPrecedence.name: wfIpTrafficFilterDSPrecedence
wfIpTrafficFilterDSPrecedence.description: Precedence of the filter. If 2 or more rules match the one with higher precedence will be applied. The lower the value of this field the higher the precedebnce.

wfIpTrafficFilterDSBytes.name: wfIpTrafficFilterDSBytes
wfIpTrafficFilterDSBytes.description: Total number of bytes this DS filter was applied to. This is the sum of lengths of all the packets that matched this filter

wfIpTrafficFilterDSOopBytes.name: wfIpTrafficFilterDSOopBytes
wfIpTrafficFilterDSOopBytes.description: Number of bytes counted as out-of profile.

wfIpForwardTable.name: wfIpForwardTable
wfIpForwardTable.description: IP Forwarding table The IP Forwarding Table obsoletes and replaces the wfIpBaseRt Table It adds knowledge of the autonomous system of the next hop, multiple next hop support, policy routing support, and supernetting. This is based on the IP Forwarding MIB presented in RFC 1354. It adds the network mask to the index.

wfIpForwardDest.name: wfIpForwardDest
wfIpForwardDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. An entry with a value of 0.0.0.0 is considered a default route. This object may not take a Multicast (Class D) address value. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the wfIpForwardMask object is not equal to x.

wfIpForwardMask.name: wfIpForwardMask
wfIpForwardMask.description: Indicates the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the wfIpForwardDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the ipForwardMask by reference to the IP Address Class. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the wfIpForwardDest object is not equal to wfIpForwardDest.

wfIpForwardPolicy.name: wfIpForwardPolicy
wfIpForwardPolicy.description: The general set of conditions that would cause the selection of one multipath route (set of next hops for a given destination) is referred to as 'policy'. Unless the mechanism indicated by wfIpForwardProtocol specified otherwise, the policy specifier is the IP TOS field. The encoding of IP TOS is ans specified by the following convention. Zero indicated the default path if no more specific policy applies. +-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+ | | | | | PRECEDENCE | TYPE OF SERVICE | 0 | | | | | +-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+ IP TOS IP TOS Field Policy Field Policy Contents Code Contents Code 0 0 0 0 ==> 0 0 0 0 1 ==> 2 0 0 1 0 ==> 4 0 0 1 1 ==> 6 0 1 0 0 ==> 8 0 1 0 1 ==> 10 0 1 1 0 ==> 12 0 1 1 1 ==> 14 1 0 0 0 ==> 16 1 0 0 1 ==> 18 1 0 1 0 ==> 20 1 0 1 1 ==> 22 1 1 0 0 ==> 24 1 1 0 1 ==> 26 1 1 1 0 ==> 28 1 1 1 1 ==> 30 Protocols defining 'policy' otherwise must ei- ther define a set of values which are valid for this object or must implement an integer- instanced policy table for which this object's value acts as an index.

wfIpForwardNextHop.name: wfIpForwardNextHop
wfIpForwardNextHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the next system en route; Otherwise, 0.0.0.0

wfIpForwardIfIndex.name: wfIpForwardIfIndex
wfIpForwardIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value which uniquely identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached.

wfIpForwardType.name: wfIpForwardType
wfIpForwardType.description: The type of route. Note that local(3) refers to a route for which the next hop is the final destination; remote(4) refers to a route for which the next hop is not the final destination.

wfIpForwardProto.name: wfIpForwardProto
wfIpForwardProto.description: The routing mechanism via which this route was learned. Inclusion of values for gateway routing protocols is not intended to imply that hosts should support those protocols.

wfIpForwardAge.name: wfIpForwardAge
wfIpForwardAge.description: The number of seconds since this route was last updated or otherwise determined to be correct. Note that no semantics of `too old' can be implied except through knowledge of the routing protocol by which the route was learned.

wfIpForwardInfo.name: wfIpForwardInfo
wfIpForwardInfo.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular routing protocol which is responsible for this route, as determined by the value specified in the route's wfIpForwardProto value. If this information is not present, its value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }, which is a syntactically valid object identifier, and any implementation conforming to ASN.1 and the Basic Encoding Rules must be able to generate and recognize this value.

wfIpForwardNextHopAS.name: wfIpForwardNextHopAS
wfIpForwardNextHopAS.description: The Autonomous System Number of the Next Hop. When this is unknown or not relevant to the protocol indicated by ipForwardProto, zero.

wfIpForwardMetric1.name: wfIpForwardMetric1
wfIpForwardMetric1.description: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's wfIpRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpForwardMetric2.name: wfIpForwardMetric2
wfIpForwardMetric2.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's wfIpRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpForwardMetric3.name: wfIpForwardMetric3
wfIpForwardMetric3.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's wfIpRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpForwardMetric4.name: wfIpForwardMetric4
wfIpForwardMetric4.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's wfIpRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpForwardMetric5.name: wfIpForwardMetric5
wfIpForwardMetric5.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's wfIpRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

wfIpNetToMediaEntryTable.name: wfIpNetToMediaEntryTable
wfIpNetToMediaEntryTable.description: The list of elements in IP's host table

wfIpNetToMediaEntry.name: wfIpNetToMediaEntry
wfIpNetToMediaEntry.description: A description of a resolved host

wfIpNetToMediaIfIndex.name: wfIpNetToMediaIfIndex
wfIpNetToMediaIfIndex.description: The interface on which this entry's equivalence is effective. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wfIpNetToMediaNetAddress.name: wfIpNetToMediaNetAddress
wfIpNetToMediaNetAddress.description: The IpAddress corresponding to the media-dependent `physical' address.

wfIpNetToMediaType.name: wfIpNetToMediaType
wfIpNetToMediaType.description: The type of mapping. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the ipNetToMediaTable. That is, it effectively dissasociates the interface identified with said entry from the mapping identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant ipNetToMediaType object.

wfUdpInDatagrams.name: wfUdpInDatagrams
wfUdpInDatagrams.description: The total number of UDP datagrams delivered to UDP users.

wfUdpNoPorts.name: wfUdpNoPorts

wfUdpInErrors.name: wfUdpInErrors

wfUdpOutDatagrams.name: wfUdpOutDatagrams
wfUdpOutDatagrams.description: The total number of UDP datagrams sent from this entity.

wfUdpTable.name: wfUdpTable
wfUdpTable.description: The UDP listener table contains information about this entity's UDP end-points on which a local application is currently accepting datagrams.

wfUdpLocalAddress.name: wfUdpLocalAddress
wfUdpLocalAddress.description: The local IP address for this UDP listener. In the case of a UDP listener which is willing to accept datagrams for any IP interface asociated with the node, the value 0.0.0.0 is used.

wfUdpMprCreate.name: wfUdpMprCreate
wfUdpMprCreate.description: Create/Delete parameter for SIAC MPR. The default is created.

wfUdpMprStartPort.name: wfUdpMprStartPort
wfUdpMprStartPort.description: Starting UDP port number for MPR address resolution.

wfUdpMprNumberOfPorts.name: wfUdpMprNumberOfPorts
wfUdpMprNumberOfPorts.description: Max number of UDP ports in mapping table.

wfUdpMprStatisticsEnable.name: wfUdpMprStatisticsEnable
wfUdpMprStatisticsEnable.description: Enable/Disable parameter for global MPR statistics collection.

wfUdpMprInPkts.name: wfUdpMprInPkts
wfUdpMprInPkts.description: Total number of packets received by MPR

wfUdpMprOutPkts.name: wfUdpMprOutPkts
wfUdpMprOutPkts.description: Total number of packets sent by MPR

wfUdpMprGenPkts.name: wfUdpMprGenPkts
wfUdpMprGenPkts.description: Total number of packets generated by MPR.

wfUdpMprMappingTable.description: The MPR Mapping table contains information regarding UDP port to IP multicast address resolution.

wfUdpMprMapMcastAddr.description: IP multicast address associated with this port.

wfUdpMprMapStatisticsEnable.description: MPR mapping entry specific statistics collection enable/disable attribute.

wfUdpMprMapInPkts.description: Total number of MPR packets received for this port.

wfUdpMprMapOutPkts.description: Total number of MPR packets sent with this port number.

wfUdpMprMapGenPkts.name: wfUdpMprMapGenPkts

wfRipInterfacePoisonedReversed.name: wfRipInterfacePoisonedReversed
wfRipInterfacePoisonedReversed.description: Specifies how the router advertises routes it has learned from a neighboring router in periodic updates subsequently sent to the neighbor. If 'Poisoned', the node implements poisoned reverse. The router now advertises routes learned from a neighbor in RIP updates subsequently sent to that neighbor with a hop count of wfRipBaseRipNetworkDiameter plus 1, (thus declaring the destination unreachable). If 'Split', the router implements a split-horizon, and omits routes learned from a neighbor in RIP updates subsequently sent to that neighbor. If 'Actual', the learned cost of the route is advertised.

wfRipIntfBroadcastTimer.name: wfRipIntfBroadcastTimer
wfRipIntfBroadcastTimer.description: This parameter allows the user to configure the frequency of full RIP updates. The default is per the standard. If DOR ( Dial Optimized Routing ) is not configured, the minimum would be every 5 seconds, with a maximum of 24 hours. If DOR is configured the minimum could be zero the maximum ( also is default ) could be two weeks (1209600);

wfRipIntfTimeoutTimer.name: wfRipIntfTimeoutTimer
wfRipIntfTimeoutTimer.description: This parameter allows the user to configure the time period which RIP will wait before timing out a route. This time is typically 3 x the broadcast timer. The default is 90 seconds with a maximum of 72 hours if DOR ( Dial Optimized Routing ) is not configured. Otherwise it could be 6 weeks( 3628800 ) as maximum value and two weeks as default value ( 1209600 ).

wfRipIntfHolddownTimer.name: wfRipIntfHolddownTimer
wfRipIntfHolddownTimer.description: This parameter allows the user to configure the time period which unreachable routes will be held in the Routing Pool. This time is typically 3 x the broadcast timer. It allows RIP to advertise the unreachable routes to help convergence time. If DOR ( Dial Optimized Routing ) is configured the default value would be 1209600 two weeks , and maximum value of 3628800 ( 6 weeks ).

wfRipIntfCompSwitch.name: wfRipIntfCompSwitch
wfRipIntfCompSwitch.description: This parameter allows the user to configure which mode of RIP to run. The default is to run RIP1. RIP2 mode runs RIP2. This does not do automatic aggregation of subnets like RIP1 does. RIP2_AGGR provides the automatic aggregation of subnets for RIP2.

wfRipIntfAuthType.description: Specifies the type of Authentication to be used with RIP. This is only valid when running RIP2

wfRipIntfAuthentication.name: wfRipIntfAuthentication
wfRipIntfAuthentication.description: Contains the authentication if the Authentication Type is set to simple password. This field contains up to 16 characters.

wfRipIntfInitStabilizationTimer.description: This parameter allows the user to cofigure the time period which RIP will use as its initial stabilization time length. It allows RIP to learn all routes from its neighbors before sending full updates.

The internal service class is 'carried' with the packet through the forwarding path, affecting various internal mechanisms (e.g. queueing, policing, clipping) and then possibly used at the egress interface to affect changes to the ToS value, which VC, etc.

wfIpTosTemplateCfgRxMapping.name: wfIpTosTemplateCfgRxMapping
